1. The web browser ask the DNS resolver an ip adress corresponding the record via a web server
2. The web browser gets back the ip address needed via the web server
3. The web browser gets finaly the static web site needed via the web browser
4. The web browser request the server with the corresponding ip address via the web server
5. The web server ask the DNS resolver the ip address for given DNS record
6. The DNS resolver respond with good ip address
7. The web server request the server with the correspondind ip address
8. The web server get the HTML/CSS (static web site) code from the corresponding server
9. The HAProxy load balancer server send a request the one of the two avariable server
10. The HAProxy load balancer get back the result like a static web site
11. At runtime the application request data from Data base
12. At runtime the application gets back the data needed